The families of five Chinese feminists detained by police for more than a month facing charges of ` picking quarrels and provoking trouble ' have issued a plea to authorities for their release .
The female activists were arrested the weekend before International Women 's Day as they were preparing to hand out leaflets about sexual harassment on public transport .
The five women have been linked to several stunts over the last few years and face being jailed for up to five years if they are charged .